CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 11, 1964, pg. 1 reads: "Health-O-Rama Begins - The first Health-O-Rama of the year began on April 9 and is continuing until Sunday, at the Savoy Ballroom, Centre Ave. and Dinwiddie St.  Shown in the let photo are some of the many persons in the community who are working to make the health fair a big success.  They are (seated, left to right) Msgr. Raymond A. Must, the Rev. Charles H. Foggie, (standing, left to right) the Rev. James A. Cox, chairman, and the Rev. J.G. Harris... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left, seated: Msgr. Raymond A. Must and Rev. Charles H. Foggie; standing: Rev. James A. Cox and Rev. J.G. Harris, gathered at table for Health-O-Rama meeting, another version
